fr.zelus.jarvis.plugins.generic_chat.platform.io

Class GenericChatIntentProvider

        • fr.zelus.jarvis.plugins.generic_chat.platform.io.GenericChatIntentProvider
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Runnable

    public class GenericChatIntentProvider
extends IntentProvider<GenericChatPlatform>
    A generic IntentProvider that wraps a concrete chatting IntentProvider.

    This class is used to define generic execution models that can be bound to specific chatting platforms through the provided Configuration.

    The specific IntentProvider wrapped by this class should be defined in the CONCRETE_CHAT_INTENT_PROVIDER_KEY property of the provided Configuration. Note that only the name of the IntentProvider is required in the Configuration, the GenericChatIntentProvider will take care of retrieving the corresponding class in its runtimePlatform's sub-platform classpath and constructing it.

    • Constructor Detail

      • GenericChatIntentProvider

        public GenericChatIntentProvider(GenericChatPlatform runtimePlatform,
                                 Configuration configuration)
        Constructs a new GenericChatIntentProvider with the provided runtimePlatform and configuration.

        This constructor initializes the concrete chatting IntentProvider from the CONCRETE_CHAT_INTENT_PROVIDER_KEY Configuration property.

        Note: this constructor will throw a JarvisException if an error occurred when building the concrete IntentProvider. The provided Configuration should contain all the IntentProvider specific properties (e.g. access tokens).

        Parameters:
        runtimePlatform - the RuntimePlatform containing this GenericChatIntentProvider
        configuration - the Configuration used to initialize the concrete IntentProvider
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if the provided runtimePlatform or configuration is null
        IllegalArgumentException - if the provided Configuration does not contain a CONCRETE_CHAT_INTENT_PROVIDER_KEY property
